d 'TOTIMPACT': module to compute total impact effects in time series regressions
d
d     totimpact estimates the total impact effect of each regressor
d in a linear time series regression, following Pesaran and Smith  
d  (2014). In an experiment the inputs are made orthogonal, so the
d effect of one input is unambiguous. In observational time   
d series the regressors are realisations of correlated stochastic
d processes that cannot be held fixed, and the ordinary   
d multiple-regression coefficient beta_i — the ceteris paribus
d (other things equal) effect — is often not the quantity of	 
d interest. 
d
d KW: time series
d KW: impact
d KW: orthogonal effects
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260708
d
f totimpact.ado
f totimpact.sthlp
f totimpact_postestimation.sthlp
f totimpact_example.do
